publicationXrefed9.standardName: Role of Osterix and MicroRNAs in Bone Formation and Tooth Development.

pathway.author: [Khanspers, Ariutta, Eweitz]

comments.content:
Role of Osx and certain miRNAs in tooth development. 

A – The role of Osx in dentinogenesis is shown by its regulation on Dspp. 

B – Osx regulates the differentiation of cementoblasts through Wnt-β-catenin pathway. 

C – Fine-tuning role of miRNA in tooth development.
